            text: "300"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'User priority, use this as reference for your own dsp units"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_DSP_DEFAULTPRIORITY_FFTUNIT
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: IntegerLiteral
            text: "900"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "           "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'This reads data for FSOUND_DSP_GetSpectrum, so it comes after user units"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_DSP_DEFAULTPRIORITY_CLIPANDCOPYUNIT
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: IntegerLiteral
            text: "1000"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "  "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'DSP CLIP AND COPY unit - last"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: EndKeyword
            text: End
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FSOUND_CAPS"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Driver description bitfields.  Use FSOUND_Driver_GetCaps to determine if a driver enumerated"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' has the settings you are after.  The enumerated driver depends on the output mode, see"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FSOUND_OUTPUTTYPES"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EnumStatement
        children:
          - kind: PublicKeyword
            text: Public
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_CAPS
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_CAPS_HARDWARE
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H1
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "       "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' This driver supports hardware accelerated 3d sound."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_CAPS_EAX2
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H2
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "           "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' This driver supports EAX 2 reverb"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_CAPS_EAX3
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H10
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' This driver supports EAX 3 reverb"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: EndKeyword
            text: End
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FSOUND_MODES"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Sample description bitfields, OR them together for loading and describing samples."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' NOTE.  If the file format being loaded already has a defined format, such as WAV or MP3, then"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' trying to override the pre-defined format with a new set of format flags will not work.  For"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' example, an 8 bit WAV file will not load as 16bit if you specify FSOUND_16BITS.  It will just"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' ignore the flag and go ahead loading it as 8bits.  For these type of formats the only flags"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' you can specify that will really alter the behaviour of how it is loaded, are the following."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Looping behaviour - FSOUND_LOOP_OFF, FSOUND_LOOP_NORMAL, FSOUND_LOOP_BIDI"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Load destination - FSOUND_HW3D, FSOUND_HW2D, FSOUND_2D"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Loading behaviour - FSOUND_NONBLOCKING, FSOUND_LOADMEMORY, FSOUND_LOADRAW, FSOUND_MPEGACCURATE, FSOUND_MPEGHALFRATE, FSOUND_FORCEMONO"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Playback behaviour - FSOUND_STREAMABLE, FSOUND_ENABLEFX"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' PlayStation 2 only - FSOUND_USECORE0, FSOUND_USECORE1, FSOUND_LOADMEMORYIOP"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' See flag descriptions for what these do."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EnumStatement
        children:
          - kind: PublicKeyword
            text: Public
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_MODES
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_LOOP_OFF
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H1
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "             "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For non looping samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_LOOP_NORMAL
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H2
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For forward looping samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_LOOP_BIDI
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H4
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "            "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For bidirectional looping samples.  (no effect if in hardware)."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_8BITS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H8
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "                "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For 8 bit samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_16BITS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H10
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For 16 bit samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_MONO
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H20
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "                "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For mono samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_STEREO
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H40
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For stereo samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_UNSIGNED
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H80
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "            "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For source data containing unsigned samples."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SIGNED
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H100
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "             "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For source data containing signed data."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_DELTA
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H200
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For source data stored as delta values."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_IT214
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H400
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For source data stored using IT214 compression."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_IT215
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H800
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For source data stored using IT215 compression."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_HW3D
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H1000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "              "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' Attempts to make samples use 3d hardware acceleration. (if the card supports it)"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_2D
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H2000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "                "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' Ignores any 3d processing.  overrides FSOUND_HW3D.  Located in software."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_STREAMABLE
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H4000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For realtime streamable samples.  If you dont supply this sound may come out corrupted."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_LOADMEMORY
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H8000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For FSOUND_Sample_Load - name will be interpreted as a pointer to data"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_LOADRAW
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H10000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For FSOUND_Sample_Load/FSOUND_Stream_Open - will ignore file format and treat as raw pcm."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_MPEGACCURATE
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H20000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "     "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For FSOUND_Stream_Open - scans MP2/MP3 (VBR also) for accurate FSOUND_Stream_GetLengthMs/FSOUND_Stream_SetTime."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_FORCEMONO
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H40000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For forcing stereo streams and samples to be mono - needed with FSOUND_HW3D - incurs speed hit"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_HW2D
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H80000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "             "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' 2d hardware sounds.  allows hardware specific effects"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_ENABLEFX
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H100000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' Allows DX8 FX to be played back on a sound.  Requires DirectX 8 - Note these sounds cant be played more than once, or have a changing frequency"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_MPEGHALFRATE
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H200000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For FMODCE only - decodes mpeg streams using a lower quality decode, but faster execution"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_XADPCM
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H400000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For XBOX only - Describes a user sample that its contents are compressed as XADPCM"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_VAG
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H800000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "             "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For PS2 only - Describes a user sample that its contents are compressed as Sony VAG format."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_NONBLOCKING
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H1000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For FSOUND_Stream_Open - Causes stream to open in the background and not block the foreground app - stream plays only when ready."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_GCADPCM
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H2000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For Gamecube only - Contents are compressed as Gamecube DSP-ADPCM format"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_MULTICHANNEL
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H4000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "   "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For PS2 only - Contents are interleaved into a multi-channel (more than stereo) format"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_USECORE0
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H8000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "       "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For PS2 only - Sample/Stream is forced to use hardware voices 00-23"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_USECORE1
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H10000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "      "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For PS2 only - Sample/Stream is forced to use hardware voices 24-47"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_LOADMEMORYIOP
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H20000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' For PS2 only - \"name\" will be interpreted as a pointer to data for streaming and samples.  The address provided will be an IOP address"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_IGNORETAGS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H40000000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' Skips id3v2 etc tag checks when opening a stream, to reduce seek/read overhead when opening files (helps with CD performance)"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_STREAM_NET
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
