          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_DOLBYDIGITAL
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "  "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The audio is played through a speaker arrangement of surround speakers with a subwoofer."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_HEADPHONE
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "     "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The speakers are headphones."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_MONO
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The speakers are monaural."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_QUAD
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The speakers are quadraphonic."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_STEREO
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The speakers are stereo (default value)."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_SURROUND
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "      "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The speakers are surround sound."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_DTS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "           "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' The audio is played through a speaker arrangement of surround speakers with a subwoofer."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_SPEAKERMODE_PROLOGIC2
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "     "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "' Dolby Prologic 2.  Playstation 2 and Gamecube only"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: EndKeyword
            text: End
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FSOUND_INIT_FLAGS"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Initialization flags.  Use them with FSOUND_Init in the flags parameter to change various behaviour."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FSOUND_INIT_ENABLESYSTEMCHANNELFX Is an init mode which enables the FSOUND mixer buffer to be affected by DirectX 8 effects."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Note that due to limitations of DirectSound, FSOUND_Init may fail if this is enabled because the buffersize is too small."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' This can be fixed with FSOUND_SetBufferSize.  Increase the BufferSize until it works."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' When it is enabled you can use the FSOUND_FX api, and use FSOUND_SYSTEMCHANNEL as the channel id when setting parameters."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EnumStatement
        children:
          - kind: PublicKeyword
            text: Public
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INITMODES
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_USEDEFAULTMIDISYNTH
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H1
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "       "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Causes MIDI playback to force software decoding."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_GLOBALFOCUS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H2
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "               "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'For DirectSound output - sound is not muted when window is out of focus."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_ENABLESYSTEMCHANNELFX
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H4
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "     "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'For DirectSound output - Allows FSOUND_FX api to be used on global software mixer output!"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_ACCURATEVULEVELS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H8
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "          "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'This latency adjusts FSOUND_GetCurrentLevels, but incurs a small cpu and memory hit"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_PS2_DISABLECORE0REVERB
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H10
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "   "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'PS2 only - Disable reverb on CORE 0 to regain SRAM"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_PS2_DISABLECORE1REVERB
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H20
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "   "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'PS2 only - Disable reverb on CORE 1 to regain SRAM"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_PS2_SWAPDMACORES
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H40
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "         "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'PS2 only - By default FMOD uses DMA CH0 for mixing, CH1 for uploads, this flag swaps them around"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_DONTLATENCYADJUST
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H80
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "        "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Callbacks are not latency adjusted, and are called at mix time.  Also information functions are immediate"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_GC_INITLIBS
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H100
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "             "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Gamecube only - Initializes GC audio libraries"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_STREAM_FROM_MAIN_THREAD
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H200
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Turns off fmod streamer thread, and makes streaming update from FSOUND_Update called by the user"
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_PS2_USEVOLUMERAMPING
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H400
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'PS2 only   - Turns on volume ramping system to remove hardware clicks."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_DSOUND_DEFERRED
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H800
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "         "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Win32 only - For DirectSound output.  3D commands are batched together and executed at FSOUND_Update."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_DSOUND_HRTF_LIGHT
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H1000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "      "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Win32 only - For DirectSound output.  FSOUND_HW3D buffers use a slightly higher quality algorithm when 3d hardware acceleration is not present."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_DSOUND_HRTF_FULL
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H2000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "       "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'Win32 only - For DirectSound output.  FSOUND_HW3D buffers use full quality 3d playback when 3d hardware acceleration is not present."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_XBOX_REMOVEHEADROOM
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H4000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'XBox only - By default directsound attenuates all sound by 6db to avoid clipping/distortion.  CAUTION.  If you use this flag you are responsible for the final mix to make sure clipping / distortion doesn't happen."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "    "
          - kind: Identifier
            text: FSOUND_INIT_PSP_SILENCEONUNDERRUN
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EqualityOperator
            text: "="
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: Ampersand
            text: "&"
          - kind: Identifier
            text: H8000
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: "  "
          - kind: EndOfLineComment
            text: "'PSP only - If streams skip / stutter when device is powered on, either increase stream buffersize, or use this flag instead to play silence while the UMD is recovering."
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
          - kind: EndKeyword
            text: End
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: EnumKeyword
            text: Enum
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FSOUND_STREAM_NET_STATUS"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' Status values for internet streams. Use FSOUND_Stream_Net_GetStatus to get the current status of an internet stream."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
